NYC Airbnb Price Prediction Pipeline
This project implements a complete, reproducible ML pipeline for predicting Airbnb listing prices in New York City. The workflow uses MLflow, Hydra, and Weights & Biases (W&B) to manage configuration, track experiments, and version data/model artifacts.

Project files are located on the branch:

https://github.com/jknow46/Deploying-a-Scalable-ML-Pipeline-with-FastAPI/tree/setup/initial (github.com in Bing)

W&B project dashboard:

https://wandb.ai/jknow46-western-governors-university/nyc_airbnb

Pipeline Overview
The pipeline consists of six modular MLflow components:

get_data – Logs the raw dataset as a W&B artifact.

basic_cleaning – Removes price outliers and invalid rows.

data_check – Validates schema, price ranges, and data drift.

train_val_test_split – Splits cleaned data into train/val/test sets.

train_random_forest – Trains a RandomForestRegressor using numeric features.

test_regression_model – Evaluates the model and logs RMSE and R².

How to Run the Pipeline
1. Create the environment
bash
conda env create -f conda.yml
conda activate mlflow-env
2. Run the full pipeline
bash
mlflow run . --env-manager=local
3. Run specific steps (optional)
bash
mlflow run . -P steps="basic_cleaning,data_check"
Configuration
All parameters (paths, thresholds, model settings, random seeds) are defined in:

Code
config.yaml
Hydra loads this automatically when running main.py.

Artifacts & Tracking
Each component logs its outputs to Weights & Biases, including:

Cleaned dataset

Train/val/test splits

Trained model

Evaluation metrics

W&B project link:

https://wandb.ai/jknow46-western-governors-university/nyc_airbnb

Model Performance
Example evaluation results:

Code
RMSE: 58.28
R2: 0.3168
Notes
The model uses numeric-only features to ensure consistent training and testing.

All MLproject files are configured for reliable MLflow execution.

The pipeline is fully reproducible end‑to‑end.

